
    OVER 418 cases of alleged corruption have been reported
through the Public Service Commission's  National
Anti-Corruption Hotline between July and September this year.This was revealed by PSC Commissioner Michael Seloane at a
media briefing held in Tshwane on Wednesday.The PSC is a government watch-dog institution tasked with
investigating, monitoring, and evaluating the organisation and administration
